Mr.
Hall,
followed.
He
had
no
fear
of
Tartar
either,
and
Tartar
had
no
ill
will
to
him.
He
snuffed
both
the
gentlemen
round,
and
then,
as
if
concluding
that
they
were
harmless,
and
might
be
allowed
to
pass,
he
